news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai falls 11% to 9,268 units in February 2023
news.para: Real estate consultant Knight Frank India in a statement said Mumbai city (area under BMC jurisdiction) saw property sales registration of 9,268 units in February 2023.

news.title: HDFC, Punjab National Bank hike lending rates
news.para: The second-biggest public sector lender, Punjab National Bank (PNB), increased its Marginal Cost of Funds Based Lending Rate (MCLR) by 10 basis points across all tenure.

news.title: Mumbai not for developers; SRA intended for public welfare: Bombay HC
news.para: Afcons Developers Ltd and Ameya Housing Private Ltd were appointed as co-developers of the slum rehabilitation project at Jogeshwari in suburban Mumbai.

news.title: Delhi HC asks centre to take call on whether to accord sanction for attachment of DMRC assets
news.para: The high court granted time to the competent authorities in the central government to take the decision in this regard and place it on record while listing the matter for further hearing on March 2.

news.title: Complete Muttathara flat complex work in 15 months: Kerala CM
news.para: ​The chief minister in the meeting urged the authorities to complete the flat complex work within 15 months. He said there should be constant monitoring for the time-bound completion of this project.

news.title: Haryana government orders probe into Panchkula's MDC plots scam
news.para: ​The scheme for the allotment was notified and issued in the year 2004. Questions were being raised on the allotment of 39 such plots. Also, 120 un-allotted plots are under scanner.

news.title: Ready to take over Reliance Home Finance by Mar 31: Authum tells SC
news.para: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi), however, opposed it alleging violation of its circular related to voting process of debenture holders (DHs).

news.title: PMAY beneficiaries in Chandigarh to pay monthly maintenance
news.para: ​​In a public notice issued on February 22, director general of town and country planning T L Satya Parkash made a clear distinction between the responsibilities of the builder and liabilities of the allottees.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government plans to create three IT concept cities
news.para: "Andhra Pradesh is making significant strides in developing its IT industry, with plans to create three IT Concept cities in Visakhapatnam, Tirupati and Anantapur," said IT minister Gudivada Amarnath.

news.title: Soon, title deeds for gramakantam lands in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: The state government has directed the district collectors to identify the actual owners of the structures during the ongoing comprehensive land survey programme to grant the title.

news.title: Gujarat passes bill to extend period for filing applications to regularise illegal constructions
news.para: "The Gujarat Regularisation of Unauthorised Development (Amendment) Bill, 2023, was brought to empower the government to extend the period, through a notification, for making an application to regularise unauthorised construction," as per the bill document.

news.title: Dalmia Cement (Bharat) bags coal mine in Madhya Pradesh
news.para: While Rungta Sons Pvt Ltd emerged as highest bidder fo a coal mine in Odisha, Samlok Industries Pvt Ltd made the highest bid for a mine in Maharashtra.

news.title: Noida to digitise 13 lakh land records from 2002-17 to check loss, theft
news.para: The move is aimed at ensuring transparency and efficiency as it takes a lot of time to search old documents, officials have said.

news.title: Viva Group's managing director granted bail in money laundering case
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) arrested Thakur in January 2021 for allegedly having diverted more than Rs 196 crore from Housing Development Infrastructure Limited (HDIL) to Viva Group through a number of defunct firms.

news.title: Work to clear debris from Supertech twin towers' site may restart soon
news.para: Work to remove the debris and breaking the basement raft was first put on hold in December 2022, when an NCR-wide construction ban was enforced due to high air pollution.
